An irregular opening played by myself. I usually play 1.e4, to create a game where sacrifices and beutiful combonations are aplenty. When I played 1.d4, I created a slow positional game, which most masters prefer.

I however, wanted to try something new, and played 1.d4.

A popular reply by black. This offers blacks best chances at a defense to the queen pawn. Other moves, such as 1.. g6 or 1... d5, would allow a positional downside, where white wins on position. Examples are white taking control of the centre, or black lacking mobility.
?! Black should play Bb4 to get good centre control, then play c5, the Nimzo-Indian Defense. With the text move, white takes control of the centre (for now).
